    <!---------------------------------- Comparative analysis ----------------------------->

    <div class="pt-5 w-60 mb-5 container">
      <h3 class="text-center font-weight-bold">Comparative analysis</h3>
      <p>For the comparative analysis I reviewed other micro-courses at educational platforms
        like Udemy, Skillshare and GA along with the tip resource for parents Parents.com.
        I used such criteria as a layout, structuring of information,
        motivation and the habit cycle (referring to the book “The power of Habits” by Charles Duhigg).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="container ">
      <div class="row align-items-center">

        <div class="col">
          <img src="images/learning-seeds/companalysis-big.png" class="w-75 my-auto mx-auto modal-image" alt="">
          <span class="click-to-enlarge"><i>Click to enlarge</i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
          <ul>
            <li>Videos and pdfs are the most common <b>content formats</b></li>
            <li>The content is chunked into <b>small pieces</b></li>
            <li>The way to <b>invest or reflect</b> can be represented by “community” section</li>
            <li>Call-to-action buttons are used as a <b>trigger</b> to start a course</li>
            <li>Users are often asked either to <b>complete the same task</b> for the second time after getting a block of knowledge or share work with others</li>
            <li>The <b>feeling of doneness</b> is an important part of <b>motivation</b>, so the indicator of progress should catch the eye</li>
            <li>All the lessons tend to end with an <b>assessment</b> of user’s retention of the material</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container pt-5 w-60 mb-5">
      <h3 class="my-5 text-center font-weight-bold">Novice user interviews</h3>
      <p class="pb-5">In order to find out the habits surrounding seeking parenting information and resources
        we conducted 4 interviews with parents who are not familiar with Learning Seeds and its methods.
        When we’ve collected all of the data, we synthesized it in two different ways.</p>
      <div class="row align-items-center">
        <div class="col px-0">
          <img src="images/learning-seeds/empathy-map.png" class="w-75 my-auto mx-0" alt="">
        </div>
        <div class="col">
          <p class="mb-1">First, I used the <b>empathy map</b> to identify what our novice user says, does, thinks and feels.
            The results have shown that our novice user:</p>
          <br>
          <p class="mb-1"><b>Says</b> that she tries not to use her mobile devices in front of kids and go online mostly at night</p>
          <br>
          <p class="mb-1"><b>Does</b> google questions she has to find out about more developmental milestones, what is normal and also the problems she faces with kids’ behavior</p>
          <br>
          <p class="mb-1"><b>Thinks</b> that resources she finds via google are not effective enough as it’s mostly people venting and sharing rather than specific advice or methods</p>
          <br>
          <p class="mb-1"><b>Feels</b> supported when sees other people having the same feelings</p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br>
      <p class="my-5 pb-4">The other method we used is creating a <b>criteria matrix</b> that allowed to go more into the details and learn people’s habits.</p>
    </div>




    <div class="container pb-5">
      <div class="row align-items-center">

        <div class="col">
          <img src="images/learning-seeds/criteria-matrix-big.png" class="w-60 my-auto mx-auto modal-image" alt="">
          <span class="click-to-enlarge"><i>Click to enlarge</i></span>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
          <h4 class="text-center font-weight-bold">Criteria matrix takeaways:</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>People tend to use a <b>phone</b> for less than 20 minutes through day and they use the <b>computer</b> for 0.5-2 hours in the evening</b></li>
            <li>Effective <b>types of content</b> for online learning: a mix of audio and visual, video, interactive features like a webinar, speaker/presentation recordings, mixing text in with video and recording.</li>
            <li>Seeing their kids thrive is what creates the "magic moment" for parents - <b>motivator</b></li>
            <li>Staying <b>focused on kids</b> and taking a step back mentally helps to manage challenging situations</li>
            <li>Discussing what’s been learned with others helps to make it an <b>actionable piece of knowledge</b> </li>
            <li>Seeing an idea with an image helps to <b>anchor it in the mind</b> to be recalled later</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>




    <!-------------------------------------- Expert User Interviews ----------------------------->

    <div class="container my-5 pb-5 w-60">
      <h3 class="pl-5 ml-5 my-5 text-center font-weight-bold">Expert User Interviews</h3>

      <div class="row align-items-center">

